longBusinessSummary: Thruvision Group plc engages in development, manufacture, and sale of passive people-screening technology in the United Kingdom, rest of Europe, the Americas, the Asia-Pacific, the Middle East, and Africa. It offers surface transportation security cameras for protecting the traveling public from terrorist attack; customs and border security cameras to check travelers for concealed contraband; entrance and public venue security cameras for screening visitors to detect weapons and explosives; loss prevention security cameras to detect and deter theft; and deployment accessories to provide operational flexibility. Its products are used in retail supply chain loss prevention, aviation and transportation security, facilities and public area protection, and customs and border control applications. The company was formerly known as Digital Barriers plc and changed its name to Thruvision Group plc in November 2017. Thruvision Group plc was incorporated in 2010 and is headquartered in Abingdon, the United Kingdom.
